(346, 'Field of Dreams', 'Universal Pictures', 'Released', 'SUR', 'LBX', '34.98', 'PG', 1989, 'Drama', '1.85:1', 2, 0, 0, 0, 'Ray Kinsella is an Iowa farmer who hears a mysterious voice telling him to turn his cornfield into a baseball diamond. He does, but the voices directions dont stop -- even after the spirits of deceased ballplayers turn up to play.'),
(347, 'Fierce Creatures', 'Jersey Films', 'Released', '5.1', '4:3', '24.98', 'PG-13', 1997, 'Comedy', '1.33:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ex-policeman Rollo Lee is sent to run Marwood Zoo, the newly acquired business of a New Zealand tycoon. In order to meet high profit targets and keep the zoo open, Rollo enforces a new fierce creatures policy, whereby only the most impressive and dangerous animals are allowed to remain in the zoo. However, the keepers are less enthusiastic about complying with these demands.'),
(348, 'Filter: Title Of DVD', 'U Ground', 'Released', '2.0', '4:3', '24.99', 'NR', 1999, 'Documentary', '1.33:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Live music and interviews with Filter records in Dublin, Ireland, and San Francisco. Songs Included are: Welcome to the Fold, One, Hey Man Nice Shot, Stuck in Here (Live - Dublin, Ireland), Dose, Under (Live - Dublin, Ireland), White Like That (Live - Dublin, Ireland and San Francisco, CA), Stuck in Here, Jurrassitol, Hey Man Nice Shot (live).'),
(349, 'Final Analysis', 'Warner Bros. Pictures', 'Released', 'SUR', '4:3', '14.98', 'R', 1992, 'Drama', '1.33:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Barr is a psychiatrist who falls in love with the sister of one of his clients. Shes beautiful and married to a gangster. She hates her husband but is unable to escape from him.'),
(350, 'Fire Down Below', 'Seagal/Nasso Productions', 'Released', '5.1', '4:3, LBX, 16:9', '19.98', 'R', 1997, 'Action', '1.85:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When an EPA representative is murdered in a small Appalachian community, EPA undercover agent Jack Taggart is sent inâ€”posing as a handyman working with a Christian relief agencyâ€”to determine what happened.'),
(351, 'Firm', 'Mirage Enterprises', 'Released', '5.1', 'LBX, 16:9', '29.99', 'R', 1993, 'Drama', '1.85:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mitch McDeere is a young man with a promising future in Law. About to sit his Bar exam, he is approached by The Firm and made an offer he doesnt refuse. Seduced by the money and gifts showered on him, he is totally oblivious to the more sinister side of his company. Then, two Associates are murdered. The FBI contact him, asking him for information and suddenly his life is ruined. He has a choice - work with the FBI, or stay with the Firm. Either way he will lose his life as he knows it. Mitch figures the only way out is to follow his own plan...'),
(352, 'First Deadly Sin', 'Artanis Productions Inc.', 'Released', 'SUR', '4:3', '14.98', 'R', 1980, 'Crime', '1.33:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A serial killer is stalking New York. Inspector Edward X. Delaney is an NYPD detective, nearing retirement, who is trying to put together the pieces of the case. Are the victims somehow linked? What does the brutal method of death signify?'),
