(984, 'Scrooged', 'Paramount', 'Released', '5.1', 'LBX, 16:9', '29.99', 'PG-13', 1988, 'Fantasy', '1.85:1', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In this modern take on Charles Dickens "A Christmas Carol," Frank Cross (Bill Murray) is a wildly successful television executive whose cold ambition and curmudgeonly nature has driven away the love of his life, Claire Phillips (Karen Allen). But after firing a staff member, Eliot Loudermilk (Bobcat Goldthwait), on Christmas Eve, Frank is visited by a series of ghosts who give him a chance to re-evaluate his actions and right the wrongs of his past.'),
